Reduces multiple values down to a single value

Source: R/summarize.R
b_summarize.Rd

Mimics dplyr::summarize using base R and rlang

b_summarize(.data, ...)

# S3 method for default
b_summarize(.data, ...)

# S3 method for split_df
b_summarize(.data, ...)

Arguments

.data

data.frame
...

Name-value pairs of summary functions

Value

data.frame

See also

quotation

Examples

airquality%>%
  bplyr::b_group_by(Month)%>%
  bplyr::b_summarize(m = mean(Temp),m1 = max(Temp))
#>   Month        m m1
#> 1     5 65.54839 81
#> 2     6 79.10000 93
#> 3     7 83.90323 92
#> 4     8 83.96774 97
#> 5     9 76.90000 93
